 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e456293a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "title: \"Quarto Folding Examples\"\n",
    "author: \"AI Collaborator\"\n",
    "date: \"2026-06-15\"\n",
    "format:\n",
    "  html:\n",
    "    toc: true\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "This file demonstrates the three primary ways to create collapsible folds inside a Quarto document.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1. Native Code Folding\n",
    "\n",
    "Below is a Python code chunk that is folded by default."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "ceb2306e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The area of the circle is 78.54\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#| code-fold: true\n",
    "#| code-summary: \"👉 Click here to reveal the Python code\"\n",
    "\n",
    "import math\n",
    "\n",
    "radius = 5\n",
    "area = math.pi * (radius ** 2)\n",
    "print(f\"The area of the circle is {area:.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2452cb4d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 2. Collapsible Callout\n",
    "\n",
    "Quarto callouts can be made collapsible with `collapse=\"true\"`. They start folded\n",
    "and expand on click.\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-note collapse=\"true\"}\n",
    "## 📝 Click to expand this note\n",
    "\n",
    "This content is hidden until you click the title. Callouts support full Markdown\n",
    "inside them, including lists and code:\n",
    "\n",
    "- First hidden point\n",
    "- Second hidden point\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "print(\"Even code blocks work inside a collapsed callout\")\n",
    "```\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-tip collapse=\"true\"}\n",
    "## 💡 A folded tip\n",
    "\n",
    "Use `collapse=\"false\"` (the default for some types) to have them open initially.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 3. Raw HTML `<details>` Fold\n",
    "\n",
    "For arbitrary collapsible content, drop straight into HTML. This works in any\n",
    "HTML output and is the most flexible option.\n",
    "\n",
    "<details>\n",
    "<summary>🔽 Click to reveal arbitrary content</summary>\n",
    "\n",
    "This block is a native browser `<details>` element. You can put **any** Markdown\n",
    "or HTML here — tables, images, math, etc.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Column A | Column B |\n",
    "|----------|----------|\n",
    "| 1        | 2        |\n",
    "| 3        | 4        |\n",
    "\n",
    "</details>\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 4. Images\n",
    "\n",
    "### Remote image\n",
    "\n",
    "A standard Markdown image pulled from the web, with a caption and sizing:\n",
    "\n",
    "![The Quarto logo](https://quarto.org/quarto.png){width=300 fig-alt=\"Quarto logo\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "### Generated image (folded code)\n",
    "\n",
    "The code that produces this plot is folded; only the resulting image shows by\n",
    "default."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "9b07328f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 277,
       "width": 566
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#| code-fold: true\n",
    "#| code-summary: \"👉 Show the plotting code\"\n",
    "#| fig-cap: \"A simple sine wave generated with matplotlib\"\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "x = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, 200)\n",
    "y = np.sin(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 3))\n",
    "plt.plot(x, y, color=\"#89b4fa\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"sin(x)\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "937a1bf7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 5. Foldable Entire Sections\n",
    "\n",
    "The previous folds only collapse a block. To fold a **whole section** — its\n",
    "heading *and* every paragraph, list, code chunk and image under it — wrap the\n",
    "section in a raw `<details>` element and put the heading text in the `<summary>`.\n",
    "\n",
    "<details>\n",
    "<summary><strong>📂 Section A — click to expand the entire section</strong></summary>\n",
    "\n",
    "Everything between the `<summary>` and the closing `</details>` is hidden until\n",
    "you click, including subheadings:\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Subsection A.1\n",
    "\n",
    "Full Markdown still works in here:\n",
    "\n",
    "- A bullet\n",
    "- Another bullet\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "print(\"A code block living inside a folded section\")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Subsection A.2\n",
    "\n",
    "And even images:\n",
    "\n",
    "![Quarto logo, folded away](https://quarto.org/quarto.png){width=200 fig-alt=\"Quarto logo\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "</details>\n",
    "\n",
    "<details open>\n",
    "<summary><strong>📂 Section B — starts expanded (note the `open` attribute)</strong></summary>\n",
    "\n",
    "Add `open` to the `<details>` tag to have a section rendered expanded by default,\n",
    "while still letting the reader collapse it.\n",
    "\n",
    "</details>"
   ]
  }
 ],
